context: Elizabeth has held many titles and honorary military positions throughout the Commonwealth, is Sovereign of many orders in her own countries, and has received honours and awards from around the world. In each of her realms she has a distinct title that follows a <a0_0>similar formula<a0_0/>: Queen of Jamaica and her other realms and territories in <b6_0>Jamaica<b6_0/>, Queen of Australia and her other realms and territories in Australia, etc. In the Channel Islands and <b5_0>Isle of Man,<b5_0/> which are <a1_0>Crown dependencies<a1_0/> rather than separate realms, she is known as <a2_0>Duke of Normandy<a2_0/> and <a3_0>Lord of Mann<a3_0/>, respectively. Additional styles include Defender of the Faith and Duke of Lancaster. When in conversation with the Queen, the practice is to <b7_0><b8_0>initially address her<b8_0/><b7_0/> as Your Majesty and thereafter as <a4_0>Ma'am<a4_0/>.
